On Dec 11, 2004, at 1:54 PM, E. Marc Coe wrote:

> My stock distributor pooped out, and my mechanic replaced it with an 
> older unit that has points.

Does it still have a vacuum advance?  Let's hope so.

> The engine has been rebuilt, and I've been breaking it in gently.  
> Changed the oil and filter at 300 miles, and now am just over 400.

You are going to get lower mileage during break-in.  As the engine gets 
stronger, your mileage will improve.

> Again, the vehicle is running great - starting right up and all.  Do 
> you think some or all of these are affecting my lousy gas mileage?  If 
> so, which ones are the most serious and need to be addressed right 
> away?

I would start by making sure your engine is in-tune.  Do the procedures 
yourself, so that you know for sure.  Your AFM could also be out of 
adjustment... does it smell like its running rich?

